race.comment: OLIVIA ROSE (10) gets her chance. Three runs this time in have all been good, placing in all of them, beaten three lengths at Kyneton when last seen 38 days ago. This looks a very winnable maiden and the map looks ideal from the soft gate. MY CATALYST (14) resumes having been well beaten on debut at Geelong last time in. She was well backed there to start $5 and has jumped out nicely leading in to this campaign. Expecting she improves this time in. PUMP THE PEDALS (4) wasn't beaten far on debut at Bendigo over 1000m, battling away in a narrow finish. Kept fresh for this, he can roll forward and take catching. SAN PUEBLO (5) has been solid this time in and should be suited getting to 1100m now. IGOTMYMINDONYOU (2) out-ran his odds on debut at Yarra Valley and has to be respected.
